name: Ramen
description: Legend has it that there are several ramen-crazed “gen X-ers” on the hunt for the best Ramen in Sydney, and they’re coming out in droves.

name: Fish and chips
description: Brits have been eating fish and chips since the 19th century. This beloved British street food is traditionally served wrapped in a piece of white paper or newspaper.

name: Shepherds pie
description: The UK is famous for its heart-warming pies, but the most comforting of these is undoubtedly shepherd’s pie.

name: Peking Roasted Duck
description: Peking duck (北京烤鸭 Běijīng kǎoyā) is a famous dish from Beijing, enjoying world fame, and considered as one of China national dishes.

name: Kung Pao Chicken
description: Kung Pao Chicken (宫保鸡丁 gōngbào jīdīng) is a famous Sichuan-style specialty, popular with both Chinese and foreigners.

name: Chicken Makhani
description: Butter chicken is mouth-watering, tender chicken, cooked in a spiced tomato sauce.

name: Samosas
description: Spiced potatoes, onions, peas, and lentils fill traditional samosas. But sometimes, they are made with ground lamb, ground beef or ground chicken.

description: Risotto is a typical northern Italian dish that can be cooked in an infinite number of ways. .
